<title type="html"><![CDATA[My recent experience with ca65, asm6, nesasm, and wla-dx]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7014&amp;p=68355#p68355"><![CDATA[
Verbose labels obscure the relevant information of what the code is doing. More noise, less signal = less readability = most cost to maintain. Being able to use local @symbols and +/- unnamed labels is what the assembler is for, to allow more concise expression of things, to do the tedious work so you don't have to (in this case, your eyes having to wade through increased noise).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=17">blargg</a> — Fri Oct 08, 2010 12:28 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
