<title type="html"><![CDATA[My recent experience with ca65, asm6, nesasm, and wla-dx]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7014&amp;p=68285#p68285"><![CDATA[
The most annoying bit about :+ and :- is that it confuses the hell out of emacs' assembly autoindent. Well, aside from the fact that they were broken in a few versions. Unfortunately, automatically rewriting the file to go from +/- to : and :+/:- isn't entirely trivial, since cases like <br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">- cmp<br />  beq +<br />  bne ++<br />+bit<br />  bvc -<br />+rts<br /></div><br /><br />get a bit tricky to convert. You can't get away with converting every - or + in the first column to a :, and prepending a : to +'s and -'s after branches, because the ca65 version of that would be<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">: cmp<br />  beq :+<br />  bne :++<br />:bit<br />  bvc :--<br />:rts<br /></div><br /><br />A 2-pass approach could probably do it though. Alternatively, someone could hack in support, though I recall the sourcebase for it being a bit messy.<br /><br />The heavyweight bit can be mitigated somewhat with a decent premade makefile and linker script.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=8">ReaperSMS</a> — Thu Oct 07, 2010 5:05 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
